@REM KEY 0 0 "Main" "Plotter"
@{U}5) The function plotter@{UU}

   Currently a simple plotter for functions of one or two variables is  imple-
mented. Only two dimensional  functions are supported  now, a second  variable
can be used for creating animated plots.

   You can open as many plotter windows as you like; each window has it's  lo-
cal settings and can display an arbitrary number of functions.

   The command @{"plot_new()" LINK "Functions.guide/FKT-PLOT-NEW"}  creates a  new plotter  without animation,  whereas
@{"plot_newanim()" LINK "Functions.guide/FKT-PLOT-NEW"} makes a new animated  plotter. These functions return a  handle
that is used to refer to the plotter in the other commands.

   To open the plotter window use the @{"plot_open()" LINK "Functions.guide/FKT-PLOT-OPEN"} command. You can add and re-
move function to the window  using the command @{"plot_addfunc()" LINK "Functions.guide/FKT-PLOT-ADDFUNC"},  @{"plot_repfunc()" LINK "Functions.guide/FKT-PLOT-REPFUNC"}
and @{"plot_delfunc()" LINK "Functions.guide/FKT-PLOT-DELFUNC"}.

   @{" * " LINK "PlotterWindow"}  Description of the window
   @{" * " LINK "PlotterMenu"}  Description of the menu
   @{" * " LINK "PlotterToolbar"}  Description of the toolbar
   @{" * " LINK "PlotterSettings"}  The settings window
   @{" * " LINK "PlotterAnim"}  Animated plots


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ® by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "PlotterWindow"
