@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual --------------------------------- Description of the window -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Plotter" "Description of the window"
@{U}5.1) Description of the window@{UU}

   The plotter window is divided into three  parts, a @{"toolbar" LINK "PlotterToolbar"} at the top,  the
plotting area and a status line at the bottom.

   A single mouse click into the plotting area display the X/Y-position  under
the mouse pointer in the status line. A double click centeres the visible area
at this position. If  you hold down  the mouse button  while moving the  mouse
pointer, you can specify a range to  zoom into. This can be a rectangular  box
or only a X-intervall, depending on the state of @{B}auto scale@{UB}.


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ® by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
